SummaryOfDirectCharitableActy.Description1: THIS OPERATING PRIVATE FOUNDATION HAS PROVIDED ROOM AND BOARD TO QUALIFYING ARTISTS AND WRITERS ON AN ISLAND IN MAINE, INSPIRING THEIR ARTISTIC ENDEAVORS.

AppicationSubmissionInfo.FormAndInfoAndMaterials: A COMPLETED APPLICATION AND SAMPLES OF WORK ARE TO BE SUBMITTED. THERE IS A $25 APPLICATION FEE.
AppicationSubmissionInfo.RestrictionsOnAwards: THE AWARD IS AN OFFER OF A RETREAT TO WRITERS, VISUAL ARTISTS, AND COMPOSERS FOR A RESIDENCY PROGRAM WHEREBY THEY ARE TO DEVOTE EIGHT HOURS A DAY, FIVE DAYS A WEEK TO THE PROGRAM.

RlnOfActyToAccomOfExemptPrps.RelationshipStatement: THERE IS A CHARGE OF $25 FOR APPLICANTS WANTING TO PARTICIPATE.
THERE WAS TWO INSURANCE RECOVERIES FOR FACILITY CASUALTIES.

ExplnOfNonFilingWithAGStmt.Statement: NON-PROFIT CORPORATIONS NEED NOT FILE TAX FORMS WITH THE STATE OF MAINE, MAINE BEING THE DOMICILIARY STATE, THE STATE OF INCORPORATION, AND THE LOCATION OF THE CORPORATION. HOWEVER, THERE IS A REQUIREMENT TO FILE AN ANNUAL REGISTRATION FORM (MNPCA 13) EACH YEAR AND THAT HAS BEEN COMPLIED WITH.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE LEASE BETWEEN THIS ENTITY AND A DISQUALIFIED PERSON IS WITHOUT A RENTAL PAYMENT REQUIREMENT. THEREFORE, THERE IS NO SELF-DEALING [IRC SEC 4941(D)(2)(C)]; THE LENDING OF MONEY BY A DISQUALIFIED PERSON, AS DEFINED IN IRC SEC 4946(A)(1)(C), IS NOT AN ACT OF SELF-DEALING, AS HERE, WERE THERE IS NO INTEREST OR OTHER CHARGE AND THE FUNDS ARE USED EXCLUSIVELY FOR THE CHARITABLE PURPOSES [IRC SEC 4941(D)(2)(B)].PROGRAM EXPENSE (DIRECT) DETAILS:PROGRAM REPAIRS & MAINTENANCE 1425PROGRAM TRANSPORTATION 922PROGRAM SUPPLIES 656PROGRAM BOAT GAS 350PROGRAM CHEF 2500PROGRAM DIESEL FUEL 1603PROGRAM FOOD 7711PROGRAM GROUNDS MAINTENANCE 241PROGRAM PROPANE FUEL 1017PROGRAM MAINLAND ELECTRICITY 98 TOTAL PROGRAM EXPENSES 16523
